td-60293e: Validate audit-log id param before Repo.get_by
Status: [open]
Type: bug | Priority: P1
Labels: review-finding, code-quality

Description:
GA.Audit.get_log/2 passes raw path id into Repo.get_by/2 (app/lib/app/audit.ex:77-81) and AuditLogController.show/2 forwards the param directly (app/lib/app_web/controllers/api/v1/audit_log_controller.ex:87-94). For malformed non-UUID IDs, Ecto can raise cast errors instead of returning {:error, :not_found}, producing a 500 for user input. Coverage currently exercises valid UUID and not-found UUID only (app/test/app_web/controllers/audit_log_controller_test.exs:194-224). Found by: Code Quality, Security, Test Coverage.

Acceptance Criteria:
GET /api/v1/audit-logs/:id with an invalid UUID string does not raise and returns a stable client error (404 or 422); add a regression test for malformed ID input; existing show endpoint behavior for valid and cross-account UUIDs remains unchanged.
